Bombing in Karachi Kills 16, Injures 35, Rescue Group Says

-- B y   K h u r r u m   A n i s
-- 
2011-04-21T19:00:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-21/bomb-blast-in-karachi-kills-16-injures-35-rescue-group-says.html
An explosion in the southern
Pakistani city of Karachi killed 16 people and injured 35,
according to the rescue group Edhi Foundation.  Express 24/7 news channel reported that the blast was the
result of a fight between two gangs for control of an illegal
gambling den in an area of the old quarters of Karachi,
according to the Press Trust of  India .  Saquib Sultan, a police officer, in a phone interview
described the explosion as a terrorist attack without further
elaboration on whether it was part of a gang rivalry.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Khurrum Anis in Karachi at 
 kkhan14@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mark Silva at 
 msilva34@bloomberg.net  